T1  - Comment on Jill Graham's Review of Managerial Ideology and the Social Control of Deviance in Organizations
AU  - Weiss, Richard M.
Y1  - 1990/07/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1990.4309475
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1990.4309475
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 556
EP  - 557
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a commentary by Richard M. Weiss on Jill Graham's review of his book ?Managerial Ideology and the Social Control of Deviance in Organizations,? from the April, 1988 issue. The author contends that Graham misrepresented the general message of the book. He explains that Graham characterized the book's review of research on the nature of alcohol problems and of workplace alcoholism programs as contradictory, incomplete, and biased. The author says that the book disconfirms the link between long-term alcohol use and loss of control.
AB  - The article presents a commentary by Richard M. Weiss on Jill Graham's review of his book ?Managerial Ideology and the Social Control of Deviance in Organizations,? from the April, 1988 issue. The author contends that Graham misrepresented the general message of the book. He explains that Graham characterized the book's review of research on the nature of alcohol problems and of workplace alcoholism programs as contradictory, incomplete, and biased. The author says that the book disconfirms the link between long-term alcohol use and loss of control.
