TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organizational Economics: An Impending Revolution in Organization Theory?
AU  - Hesterly, William S.
AU  - Liebeskind, Julia
AU  - Zenger, Todd R.
Y1  - 1990/07/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1990.4308822
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1990.4308822
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 402
EP  - 420
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Organizational economics (OE) is purported to offer a potential revolution in organization theory. This paper assesses the value of organizational economics for organization theorists. The conclusions are that OE is useful in extending theory building and empirical research in organization theory, but for OE to realize its full potential, it must draw upon organization theory to refine theory building and expand its scope.
AB  - Organizational economics (OE) is purported to offer a potential revolution in organization theory. This paper assesses the value of organizational economics for organization theorists. The conclusions are that OE is useful in extending theory building and empirical research in organization theory, but for OE to realize its full potential, it must draw upon organization theory to refine theory building and expand its scope.
